where does Starr's investigation go? Starr could still call
witnesses before the grand jury to see if they can contradict
Clinton. He might recall Monica Lewinsky for that purpose. It is
especially likely that Starr would summon Bruce Lindsey, deputy
White House counsel who is a key Clinton advisor, since he fought
in court here for the right to question him. But over the next few
weeks, Starr is expected to shift most of his attention from
evidence collecting to evidence sifting as he combs through the
facts and testimony for any ``substantial and credible
information'' that ``may constitute grounds for impeachment.'' By
Lizette Alvarez.
