   &UR; BUSINESS DAY _ (Moved in ``f'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   PITNEY-BOWES (Stamford, Conn.) _ Michael Critelli well remembers
the uncertainty he faced when he became chief executive of Pitney
Bowes Inc. two years ago. Investors were worried that faxes would
kill regular mail, then e-mail would kill faxes, and finally, all
these changes would kill Pitney's profits. Actually, the company
has kept its footing quite well. But does that mean that
predictions of mail's demise _ and thus, of Pitney's fall _ are
wrong? Or are they merely premature? By Claudia H. Deutsch.
</P>
