<P>
   &UR; CULTURE (Moved in ``e'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FEZ-RESTORE (Fez, Morocco) _ Fez is an ancient place but also a
functioning city, and one in need of repair. Several years ago
Unesco named it a Heritage of Mankind City, like the Old City of
Jerusalem. But a major difference between the old walled city, or
medina, of Fez and almost all other ancient city centers in this
part of the world is that it remains the hub of the local economy.
The problem here is how to fix up the medina without fundamentally
changing it, how to preserve it as a religious and economic center.
By Michael Kimmelman.
</P>
<P>
   MAINE-MUSIC (Islesford, Maine) _ Arts in America: Bringing music
to outlying communities in Maine. By Paula Deitz.
