Lauren. Called DKNY Under Wear, the line was unveiled in New York
last week. A report.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BUSINESS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``FROM MONICA TO O.J., CELEBRITY ENDORSERS CAN BE RISKY
BUSINESS'' From WWD. What happens when celebrities are caught in
compromising positions while wearing designer labels with which
they have no commercial association? For example, Hugh Grant
wearing a Tommy Hilfiger cap when arrested for soliciting a
prostitute, or O.J. Simpson wearing the infamous Bruno Maglis.
Companies executives discuss the impact of these unplanned product
placements. A report.
</P>
<P>
   Thank you.
</P>
