r k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-COMMENTARY-BJT19-COX     08-18 0404
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COMMENTARY-BJT19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE WEDNESDAY COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Wednesday, August 19, 1998, are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ With the admission he lied about his
relationship with Monica Lewinsky, President Bill Clinton goes from
lame duck to dead duck. The Clinton presidency is over and the
president would do best to resign and let Vice President Al Gore
start a new slate. (Teepen, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ Ever so slowly, at a steady but glacier-like
pace, everything seemingly believable becomes unbelievable. Even
the stories that render other stories implausible become
implausible themselves. How many Americans will swear to you that
Elvis is alive? Did Shirley McLaine have anything to do with the
French Revolution? Howard Kleinberg is a former editor of the Miami
News. (Kleinberg, Cox News Service) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA, Fla. _ I like virtual moving day much
better than real moving day. No boxes to schlep around. Fewer
orthopedic dangers. You don't have to bribe friends into carrying
things by passing out pizza and beer. You just swap floppies back
and forth. (Lane, Daytona Beach News-Journal) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KABAT-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ I am eager to begin this next phase
of my life. I have been fortunate all these years to be able to
balance my time between children and work. Now, however, with our
eldest son heading off the college, the time has come for me to
increase my take-home ... and I don't mean his dirty laundry each
week. (Kabat, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Have you heard about the guy
in Clearwater, Fla. who is suing a topless nightclub because,
according to his story, he suffered whiplash when a dancer
unleashed her 60-HH bust and jumped up and slammed her breasts into
the victim's head? Although it may sound like it, don't think I'm
taking all of this lightly. Let me make (ITAL)this(END ITAL)
politically correct statement about (ITAL)that(END ITAL): I feel
his pain. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
