</P>
<P>
   Collio Restaurant, in the Hotel Triest at 12 Wiedner
Hauptstrasse, (43-1) 589-18-133, takes some of its culinary
inspiration from Trieste, which used to serve the Austro-Hungarian
Empire. Designed by Terence Conran, the long room with blue chairs
and metal tabletops extends into the garden, where dinner is also
served until the fall. Lamb tenderloin with olive crust and thyme
sauce is one of the chef's specialties. A meal for two with wine
costs about $95.
</P>
<P>
   A wine bar and wine store are part of Zum Finsteren Stern (To
the Dark Star), which is on a small cobbled street at 3-5
