<HEADLINE>
KEEPING TIME WITH PRESIDENT CLINTON 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By STEVE BARNES  
 c.1998 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. _ Even before President Clinton admitted Monday
that he had a ``personal relationship'' with Monica Lewinsky, polls
showed the majority of Americans believed that the president had
been less than forthcoming about his ties with the former White
House intern. And now along comes a wristwatch with an opinion on
the subject. The quartz timekeeper, from Seattle's Worldwide Watch
Co., features a caricature of Clinton against an American-flag
backdrop. Under-the-dial animation produces the effect of Clinton's
nose tripling in length every 10 seconds, after which it returns to
normal size and grows again. Although the $30 Clinton Nose Growing
Watch won't be in stores until the end of the year, it is available
now by calling 800-535-0131 or visiting a site on the World Wide
Web, http://www.worldwidewatch.com.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _____ &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FRIGHTENING FURNITURE
</P>
<P>
   That lamentable sofa you've relegated to the basement or donated
to some fraternity house's rumpus room may finally be worth
something _ $2,000, in fact. That's the prize for winning the
annual Ugly Couch Contest, sponsored by Sure Fit Inc., the nation's
largest maker of sofa slipcovers. Pictured is last year's hideous
winner. To enter the contest, take a good-quality color photo of
your appalling couch, write a short poem about it and mail both to:
Lee Barry, Sure Fit Inc., 58 W. 40th St., 2nd Floor, New York, NY
10018. Creative entries are encouraged. Past winners have, for
example, sent along boxfuls of items found in their couch's
crevices. The winner gets the two grand; runners-up receive
slipcovers to disguise their award-winning couches. Sure Fit
slipcovers are marketed nationally under the Fieldcrest and Cannon
brands.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _____ &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   KOJAK CONFAB
</P>
<P>
   The Bald Is Beautiful convention will be held Sept. 11-13 in
Morehead City, N.C. The affair is the 25th such annual gathering
and is thus dubbed the Silver Dome Anniversary for the Bald-Headed
Men of America club. Lacking hair apparently inclines one toward
jokey statements such as the following, contained in the convention
announcement: ``Ours is the only organization that grows because of
lack of growth,'' and ``Morehead City _ where Morehead definitely
means `less hair.''' Last year's convention attracted 200 men (and
a few women). Of the 40 million baldies in the nation, half are
baby boomers who are at or approaching age 50. To make a
reservation, call the club at 252-726-1855 or call the Morehead
City Hampton Inn directly at 252-240-2300 and ask for the special
``bald'' rate.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
