<SLUG> BC-BBO-MINORS-SYSTEM-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    MINOR LEAGUE SERIES: The Braves' farm system
 &HT;    By Guy Curtright
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Braves have one of the largest player-development programs
in baseball, with eight farm teams. Only five other major-league
organizations have as many, and some have only six. Atlanta owns
six of its eight teams, also a major-league high:
</P>
<P>
   Dominican Summer League
</P>
<P>
   City: San Pedro de Macoris, Dominican Republic.
</P>
<P>
   Nickname: Braves.
</P>
<P>
   Ownership: Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Class: Rookie level.
</P>
<P>
   Schedule: 72 games from June through August.
</P>
<P>
   Manager: Pedro Gonzalez.
</P>
<P>
   Players: 17- to 19-year-olds from the Dominican Republic and
Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
   Salaries. $850-$1,000 per month for three months.
</P>
<P>
   Meal money: none.
</P>
<P>
   Gulf Coast League
</P>
<P>
   City: Orlando at Disney's Wide World of Sports complex.
</P>
<P>
   Nickname: Braves.
</P>
<P>
   Ownership: Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Class: Rookie level.
</P>
<P>
   Schedule: 60 games from June through August.
</P>
<P>
   Manager: Rick Albert.
</P>
<P>
   Players: 17- to 21-year-olds from 10 countries, most in first
season.
</P>
<P>
   Salaries: $850-$1,000 per month for three months.
</P>
<P>
   Meal money: none.
</P>
<P>
   Appalachian League
</P>
<P>
   City: Danville, Va.
</P>
<P>
   Nickname: Braves.
</P>
<P>
   Ownership: Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Class: Advanced rookie level.
</P>
<P>
   Schedule: 68 games from June through August.
</P>
<P>
   Manager: Franklin Stubbs.
</P>
<P>
   Players: 18- to 21-year-olds, most in first or second season.
</P>
<P>
   Salaries: $850-$1,000 per month for three months.
</P>
<P>
   Meal money: $15 per day on overnight trips.
</P>
<P>
   Northwest League
</P>
<P>
   City: Eugene, Ore.
</P>
<P>
   Nickname: Emeralds.
</P>
<P>
   Ownership: Elmore Sports Group.
</P>
<P>
   Class: Short-season Class A.
</P>
<P>
   Schedule: 76 games from June through August.
</P>
<P>
   Manager: Jim Saul.
</P>
<P>
   Players: 18- to 23-year-olds, first-year college draftees and
second- or third-year high school draftees.
</P>
<P>
   Salaries: $850-$1,000 per month for three months.
</P>
<P>
   Meal money: $15 per day on overnight trips.
</P>
<P>
   South Atlantic League
</P>
<P>
   City: Macon, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Nickname: M-Braves.
</P>
<P>
   Ownership: Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Class: Lower-level Class A.
</P>
<P>
   Schedule: 142 games from April through August.
</P>
<P>
   Manager: Brian Snitker.
</P>
<P>
   Players: 19- to 23-year-olds, with two to four years of pro
experience.
</P>
<P>
   Salaries: $1,000-$1,200 per month for five months.
</P>
<P>
   Meal money: $15 per day on the road.
</P>
<P>
   Carolina League
</P>
<P>
   City: Danville, Va.
</P>
<P>
   Nickname: 97s.
</P>
<P>
   Status: Team will move to Myrtle Beach, S.C., next season and
will be called Pelicans.
</P>
<P>
   Ownership: Capitol Broadcasting.
</P>
<P>
   Class: Advanced-level Class A.
</P>
<P>
   Schedule: 140 games from April to early September.
</P>
<P>
   Manager: Paul Runge.
</P>
<P>
   Players: 19- to 24-year-olds, with three to five years of pro
experience.
</P>
<P>
   Salaries: $1,100-$1,300 per month for five months.
</P>
<P>
   Meal money: $15 per day on the road.
</P>
<P>
   Southern League
</P>
<P>
   City: Greenville, S.C.
</P>
<P>
   Nickname: G-Braves.
</P>
<P>
   Ownership: Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Class: Class AA.
</P>
<P>
   Schedule: 140 games from April to early September.
</P>
<P>
   Manager: Randy Ingle.
</P>
<P>
   Players: 19- to 26-year-olds, some with major-league experience.
</P>
<P>
   Salaries: $1,400-$2,000 per month for five months; some veteran
minor leaguers occasionally make more.
</P>
<P>
   Meal money: $17 per day on the road.
</P>
<P>
   International League
</P>
<P>
   City: Richmond.
</P>
<P>
   Nickname: R-Braves.
</P>
<P>
   Ownership: Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Class: Class AAA.
</P>
<P>
   Schedule: 144 games from April to early September.
</P>
<P>
   Manager: Max Venable, interim.
</P>
<P>
   Players: 20- to 31-year-olds, many with major-league experience.
</P>
<P>
   Salaries: $2,100-$10,000 per month for five months. Optioned
major-leaguers on long-term contracts make more.
</P>
<P>
   Meal money: $18 per day on the road.
</P>
<P>
   Guy Curtright writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
