all sluglines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HATE-CRIMES (Washington) _ A leading expert on hate crimes, New
York University law professor James B. Jacobs, says laws against
them are not needed because ``crimes are crimes'' and motivation
based on bias should not result in longer sentences for defendants.
His comments during a debate are disputed. By NICOLE TSONG.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ President Clinton's angry attack on
Independent Counsel Kenneth Starr during his confession of an
inappropriate relationship with Monica Lewinsky indicates that the
president may be cornered but he's still a fighter. He moves into
the next phase of the scandal in a combative mood as the House
prepares to cope with Starr's report. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
