<HEADLINE>
TASTINGS HEFT, LENGTH 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Enfolds Yattarna Chardonnay 1995, South Australia. About $50. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   John Duval, the chief winemaker at Penfolds, says this is the
white wine equivalent of the winery's legendary Grange, whose
reputation as Australia's finest red wine has never been seriously
challenged. Grange, first released in 1955, has a track record;
this, the first commercialized vintage of Yattarna, has not.
</P>
<P>
   The grapes come from Adelaide Hills and McLaren Vale vineyards.
Aging was 10 months in French oak, some new, some used once before.
</P>
<P>
   This is a spectacular wine. It is profoundly rich; it has heft
and length and, at this stage of its development, beautiful
balance. It holds out the promise of considerable elegance a few
years hence.
</P>
<P>
   As the song says, this could be the start of something big.
</P>
</TEXT>
