<P>
   SANTA FE-OPERA &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SANTA FE, N.M. _ It's two shows for the price of one. Nowhere do
opera and creation mingle so harmonically as the New Mexican high
desert. Since 1957, the outdoor Santa Fe Opera has been known as
much for its sublime locale as its artistic merit and adventuresome
spirit. Cradled in a natural amphitheater 10 minutes north of the
city, the opera delights in its relationship with the land and sky.
Lightning punctuates arias. Chilly evening breezes toy with the
sopranos' skirts. By LIZ STEVENS. Story has moved in ``l''
lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ANDERSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The first day of school has come and gone without a
hitch. Hooray. My kids actually said it was ``OK.'' I can live with
that. We all know that the first day of most anything is an
incredibly anxious time. The first day on the new job, the first
day at boot camp, the first day as a parent _ all produce a certain
degree of heart pounding and stomach churning. By MONICA ANDERSON.
Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
