now to have waned, and the list soon may be almost forgotten. But
of necessity, there will be postscripts, and here's one. Along with
a few hundred others who watch the book scene and work on its
periphery, I got in my licks and supposed I was done with the
issue. But three readers _ two women, one man _ contacted me by
letters (the women) and by telephone (the man), all on the matter
of Rebecca West. By LARRY SWINDELL. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
