KIDS INVITED TO `SAY THE DARNDEST THINGS'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEITH MARDER 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Face it, your kid is cuter than other kids, and
nothing but precious pearls roll off that witty little tongue.
Everyone knows it.
</P>
<P>
   Well, now you can put your child's mouth where the funny is.
``Kids Say the Darndest Things'' will be looking for children for
upcoming shows between noon and 4 p.m. Sunday at the Los Angeles
Children's Museum.
</P>
<P>
   The show's producers are looking for kids ages 4 to 12. The
Children's Museum is at 310 N. Main St., downtown Los Angeles. The
$5 admission to the museum is necessary to try out for the show.
</P>
