been full of uprisings, is likely to be decided by more powerful
neighbors. These countries have sharply divergent interests, but
one trait in common: during the rebellion that brought Kabila to
power, they grew used to playing kingmaker in Africa's third
largest country. By Howard W. French. (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m.
