 &HT;    Braves on deck: San Francisco Giants
 &HT;    By I. J. Rosenberg
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 7:40 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   TV: Fox Sports South.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: LHP Tom Glavine (16-4, 2.35, 13-10,
3.38 ERA lifetime vs. Giants) vs. RHP Mark Gardner (9-5, 4.89; 5-5,
4.13 ERA lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Glavine tries to become the league's first 17-game
winner. . . . Since July 12, Glavine has brought his ERA down from
2.85 to 2.35. He has won four in a row and in his last six starts
has allowed just five runs on 25 hits. . . . On Aug. 7, Glavine
beat the Giants in San Francisco, going nine innings and allowing
no runs on three hits. . . . Lifetime, the Giants are hitting just
.238 against Glavine. . . . Barry Bonds hits .317 against Glavine
with three homers and 13 at-bats in 63 at-bats. Charlie Hayes is
hitting .327 (16-for-49) off Glavine. Stan Javier is just 2-for-27.
. . . Gardner faced the Braves on Aug. 9, allowing five runs on
just four hits but not getting a decision. . . . Gardner's ERA of
4.89 is his lowest since it was 3.75 after the second start of the
season. . . . Gardner is 4-2 on the road with a 4.35 ERA. He is 8-4
on grass. . . . Lifetime, the Braves are hitting .238 against
Gardner. . . . Chipper Jones has eight hits in 20 at-bats with two
homers against Gardner, while Ryan Klesko is 2-for-21.
</P>
