<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Minors see major fan boost
 &HT;    By Guy Curtright
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The major leagues are still trying to win back fans lost because
of the 1994 players' strike, but baseball is booming in the minors.
</P>
<P>
   Attendance at minor-league games averaged a record 3,475 last
season, continuing a revival that began in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
   The total attendance of 34,721,716 for 16 leagues was nearly a
60 percent increase from 10 years earlier and more than double the
figure of 20 years ago. The only time the minors drew more was the
late 1940s, when there were more than three times as many teams.
</P>
<P>
   Minor-league franchises, which had been guaranteed money losers,
now sell for as much as $8 million in Class AAA and $6 million in
Class AA. Even Class A teams go for $2 million to $3 million.
</P>
<P>
   Most minor-league teams are privately owned, but Atlanta owns
three of its top four farm teams _ Richmond, Greenville and Macon.
</P>
<P>
   Class AAA Richmond and Class AA Greenville both are heading
toward franchise attendance records, even though the teams have
losing records.
</P>
<P>
   In the top 10 of minor-league attendance every season since the
12,000-seat Diamond opened in 1985, Richmond is on pace to better
its record of 540,489 set in 1993. The International League team is
averaging 7,390 per game.
</P>
<P>
   Greenville has drawn 224,244 for 56 dates, an average of 4,004.
The Southern League team's franchise record is 254,049 set last
year.
</P>
<P>
   Macon also would be in range of a franchise attendance mark if
not for five rainouts. The M-Braves' record is 129,723, set last
year. Macon, averaging 1,828, has drawn 109,688 this year with six
games left in the Class A South Atlantic League season.
</P>
<P>
   The minor-league attendance leader is Buffalo, averaging 10,478
in the International League. Buffalo is the only minor-league team
to draw 1 million in a season. The Bisons did it six years in a
row.
</P>
<P>
   COMPARING ATTENDANCE
</P>
<P>
   Team Class Avg.
</P>
<P>
   Richmond AAA 7,390
</P>
<P>
   Greenville AA 4,004
</P>
<P>
   Eugene A 3,660
</P>
<P>
   Macon A 1,826
</P>
<P>
   Danville Braves R 1,756
</P>
<P>
   Danville 97s A 1,187
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
</TEXT>
